race.comment: SUNSET MISSILE (3) was dominant last start at Mornington, controlling throughout and putting a space on rivals over the staying trip. Clearly thriving and looks the hardest to beat. MATTHEW MARK (8) bounced back with a strong second at Hamilton and while the rise in trip is a query, he's in the right race to make his presence felt. NORTHERN BARRAGE (4) wasn't far away at Geelong after scoring the run prior. Easier here and drawn to get every chance. SANDPIPER (11) continues to race well and is edging closer to a breakthrough. The trip is the test but she deserves her shot. HOLLY'S STAR (6) was a barnstorming winner fresh and this is easier than her latest assignment. Capable of bouncing back.
